Chocolate Chip - Banana Bread
Last made: 2024-12-23
Servings: one loaf (12 servings)
Estimated Prep Time: 15 minutes
Cook Time: 1 hour 10 minutes 

Ingredients:
    2 cups all-purpose flour
    1 teaspoon baking powder
    1/2 teaspoon baking soda
    1/2 teaspoon salt
    1/2 teaspoon ground cinnamon
    1/4 teaspoon ground nutmeg
    1/2 cup butter, softened
    1 cup sugar
    2 eggs
    1 teaspoon vanilla extract
    2 ripe bananas, mashed
    3/4 cup semisweet chocolate mini-morsels
    1/2 cup chopped walnuts (optional)


Instructions:
1. Grease a 9x5x3-inch loafpan.  Preheat oven to 350 degrees (F).
2. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, and nutmeg.  Set aside.
3. Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well with an electric hand mixer on medium speed.  Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.  Stir in vanilla and bananas.  Gradually add flour mixture to creamed mixture, beating until blended.  Stir in mini-morsels and walnuts.
4. Spoon batter into loafpan.  Bake for 1 hour, then cover with foil.  Bake for 10 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in the center comes out clean.  Cool in pan 10 minutes;  remove from pan, and cool completely on a wire rack.

(Adapted from Connie Burgess' recipe printed in "Southern Living")
